summary: I was watching the 90s Moomins, and recently I watched the newest Moominvalley and I really appreciate what they did with Little...
body: I was watching the 90s Moomins, and recently I watched the newest Moominvalley and I really appreciate what they did with Little My. In the 90s one she is this stereotypical younger child that gets excluded from the games of older kids, but in the newer one she is actually a character with integrity and is, like, emotionally mature. Imstead of just wrecking havoc, she moves the plot forwards and drives character development in others. I really prefer her newer portrayal because in the 90s one, I keep swinging between loathing and pitying.

Book Snufkin: I'm gonna be frank with you because the world sucks and I have my own glossed over problems.

body:
Book Snufkin: I’m gonna be frank with you because the world sucks and I have my own glossed over problems.

90s Snufkin: I’m one of the most competent people I know until the plot calls for it, but other than that I’m fine. Nothing really bothers me. Moomin is just a colleague.
